  "doc_id": "4241",
  "text": "A previous study by Winter et al [CITATION_1] showed that two different groups of stakeholders existed within UIQ. The first group was designated as Designers represented by e.g. interaction designers and system and interaction architects, representing the shop floor perspective. The second group was designated as Product Owners, including management, product planning, and marketing, representing the management perspective. These two groups were found to have different needs regarding the presentation of test results. These differences concerned the level of detail included in the presentation, the ease with which the information can be interpreted, and the presence of contextual information included in the presentation. Designers prioritised presentations that gave specific information about the device and its features, whilst Product Owners prioritised presentations that gave more overarching information about the product as a whole, and that were not dependent on including contextual information.",
